EAScenario.name: Overview of 3 assets
EAScenario.description:
Configure 3 assets in the Management Client
Check that the operator has an overview of all three managed assets.
Check that for each managed asset the Actual Load, Emergency Situation an d Emergency situation (Maintenance) is shown.
Check that for each Emenrgency situation 2 time intervals are shown with a corresponding current.
Check that the operator can select all three (one at a time) managed assets
Check that the oprator gets an indication which managed asset is selected
Check that all managed assets are displayed at the bottom of the screen.

EAScenario.name: Alarms
EAScenario.description:
- Put kabel_invoer.txt file in 'Data' directory - Start EMS Importer - Start DRS Engine when EMS importer starts logging - Start Smart Client
- Check that initially no alarms are present - Check that when the measured current exceeds 300 ampere that a warning for the measured current is raised - Alarm popup contains the warning - Alarm history contains the warning - An e-mail is sent to the configured user. - The subject of the email gives a short description of the (pre-)alarm - The right template has been used - The alarm status for the asset indicates a warning (orange) - The aggragated alarm status indicates that a warning is present.
- Check that when the measured current exceeds 400 ampere that an alarm for the measured current is raised - Alarm popup contains the alarm - Alarm history contains the alarm - An e-mail is sent to the configured user. - The subject of the email gives a short description of the (pre-)alarm - The right template has been used - The alarm status for the asset indicates an alarm (red) - The aggragated alarm status indicates that an alarm is present.
- Check that when the measured current becomes 400 ampere or less that the alarm for the measured current gets asset status 'inactive' - Alarm popup contains the alarm with asset status 'inactive'. - Alarm history contains the alarm with asset status 'inactive'. - The alarm status for the asset indicates a warning (orange) - The aggragated alarm status indicates that a warning is present. - The inactive alarm is paced below the active alarms.
- Check that when the measured current becomes 300 ampere or less that the warning for the measured current gets asset status 'inactive' - Alarm popup contains the alarm with asset status 'inactive'. - Alarm history contains the alarm with asset status 'inactive'. - The alarm status for the asset indicates normal situation (blue) - The aggragated alarm status indicates that no warning or alarm is present
EAScenario.subject: EAID_21C7A183_1F76_44ab_8F29_A3E82A1FE86D

EAScenario.name: Verify aggregated alarms

When a pre-alarm or alarm occurs acknowledge the alarm

EAScenario.name: Verify alarm history
EAScenario.description:

No assets are displayed in alarm history.
Do not acknowledge the first two alarms! Verify that when an alarm is raised it appears in the alarm history as unacknowledged. Verify that when the alar is acknowledged this is indicated in the alarm history Verify that when a pre-alarm becomes active it is displayed in the color orange in the alarm history Verify that when an larm becomes active it is displayed in the color red in the alarm history Verify that when alarm and pre-alarm become inactive it is displayed in the color grey in the alarm history Verify that an inactive alarm is placed below all active alarms
When all data is processed acknowledge all unacknowledged alarms Verify that when an inactive alarm is acknowledged it will disappear from the alarm history

- Check that initially no alarms are present - Check that when the calculated temperature exceeds 35 degress Celsius (but below 80 degress Celsius) that a warning for the hotspot temperature is raised - Do not acknowledge the alarm - Alarm popup contains the warning - Alarm history contains the warning - Alarm popup is shown on top of all other windows - An e-mail is sent to the configured user. - The subject of the email gives a short description of the (pre-)alarm - The right e-mail template has been used - The alarm status for the asset indicates a warning (orange) - The aggragated alarm status indicates that a warning is present.

- Check that when the calculated temperature becomes 35 degress Celsius or less that the alarm becomes inactive - Do not acknowledge the alarm - Alarm popup contains the warning with asset status 'inactive' - Alarm history contains the warning with asset status 'inactive' - The alarm status for the asset indicates normal situation (blue) - The aggragated alarm status indicates that no warning or alarm is present.
